#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:47
msgid ""
"This tool works only with meshes. In *Edit Mode*, the button for the "
"*Screw* tool operation is located in the *Mesh Tools* panel, "
":menuselection:`Toolbar --> Mesh Tools --> Add: Screw`. To use this tool,"
" you need to create at least one open profile or line to be used as a "
"vector for the height, and an angular vector to specify a direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:53
msgid ""
"The *Screw* tool uses two points given by the open line to create an "
"initial vector to calculate the height and basic angle of the translation"
" vector that is added to the \"Spin\" for each full rotation (see "
"examples below). If the vector is created with only two vertices at the "
"*same* XYZ location (which will not give Blender a vector value for "
"height), this will create a normal \"Spin\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:58
msgid ""
"Having at least one vector line, you can add other closed support "
"profiles that will follow this vector during the extrusions (see "
"`Limitations`_). The direction of the extrusions is calculated by two "
"determinant factors, the point of view in Global Space and the position "
"of the cursor in the 3D View using Global coordinates. The profile and "
"the vector must be fully selected in *Edit Mode* before you click the "
"*Screw* button (see `Limitations`_). When you have the vector for the "
"open profile and the other closed profiles selected, click the *Screw* "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:68
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:70
msgid ""
"There are strict conditions about the profile selection when you want to "
"use this tool. You must have at least one open line or open profile, "
"giving Blender the starting Vector for extrusion, angular vector and "
"height (e.g. a simple edge, a half circle, etc.). You need only to ensure"
" that at least one reference line has two \"free\" ends. If two open "
"Lines are given, Blender will not determine which of them is the vector, "
"and will then show you an error message, ``\"You have to select a string "
"of connected vertices too\"``. You need to select all of the profile "
"vertices that will participate in the *Screw* tool operation; if they are"
" not properly selected, Blender will also show you the same message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:81
msgid ""
"Note that the open line is always extruded, so if you only use it to "
"\"guide\" the screw, you will have to delete it after the tool completion"
" (use linked-selection, :kbd:`Ctrl-L`, to select the whole extrusion of "
"the open line)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc/screw.rst:85
msgid ""
"If there is any problem with the selection or profiles, the tool will "
"warn you with the error message: ``\"You have to select a string of "
"connected vertices too\"`` as seen in Fig. :ref:`fig-mesh-screw-error-"
"info` and Fig. :ref:`fig-mesh-screw-error-popup`, both in the "
":doc:`Status Bar </interface/window_system/status_bar>` and at the place "
"where you clicked to start performing the operation (when you click the "
"Screw Button)."
